ocal observables. However, for perturbations that\npreserve the symmetry, we show stability of the gap and the structure of the\nbroken symmetry phases. We prove that the GNS Hamiltonian associated with each\npure state has a non-zero spectral gap above the ground state.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Oct 2020 03:24:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Oct 2020 04:04:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 11 Jun 2021 22:53:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-04"}
